******
[2]
Date: Wed 15 Aug 2018, 6:31 PM
Source: Trend News Agency [edited]
https://en.trend.az/casia/kyrgyzstan/2940798.html


An emergency operations center has been established in the Kara-Kulja District of Kyrgyzstan to eliminate and localize anthrax, Press Secretary of the Ministry of Health Jyldyz Yerkinova told RIA Novosti on [Wed 15 Aug 2018]. Sanitary and preventive measures are being carried out, said Yerkinova.

Earlier, the Ministry of Health announced the hospitalization of 12 people in Kara-Kulja with suspected anthrax. All hospitalized people had had contact with meat of the infected animal.

"Anti-epidemic and anti-epizootic measures are being carried out in conjunction with the veterinary service of the district in order to localize and eliminate anthrax," said Yerkinova.

