[Osh is in the base of the lower fork of the westernmost provinces of Kyrgyzstan; see: http://legacy.lib.utexas.edu/maps/commonwealth/kyrgyzstan_physio-2005.jpg. Kara-Kudja is in eastern Osh near the Jalal-Abad border, where livestock is most common in the country; see: http://www.fallingrain.com/world/KG/08/KaraKuldzha.html.

The area is a long narrow valley so I think we can presume that annual anthrax vaccination of the livestock is not an every day event. And this would explain why the report focuses on the human cases. - Mod.MHJ

HealthMap/ProMED map available at:
Osh Oblast, Kyrgyzstan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5968018,613]
